It makes little sense that the property verb 'aware' should be an Sa verb, but the translation suggests that the meaning implied ('worry') actually includes a more agentive argument than the gloss would lead us to think. However, there are also other verbs for which I can't think of an explanation right away, such as *yami*, 'be unconscious', as in (<!--\ref{tariana-case}-->b) below, which also should not be an Sa verb. I can only conclude this issue by saying that while in Tariana split intransitivity seems to generally be sensitive to property verbs, there are some inconsistencies, and more in-depth research would be needed to assess whether these represent merely some idiosyncratic exceptions or have other reasons (similar to the Spanish loanwords in Guaraní ... see section ??), or whether agentivity plays some role; and similarly this would beg the question as to whether such a thing were unique to Tariana or might be shared by other Arawak languages as well.

